# Banggood Product Scraper & Analyzer

A comprehensive web scraping project that extracts product data from Banggood, performs data cleaning and transformation, and provides exploratory analysis through an interactive Streamlit dashboard.

## üìã Project Overview

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  subgraph Repo["GitHub Repository"]
    direction TB
    NB[/"scraper.ipynb\n(Selenium scraper)"/]
    CSV["banggood_products_cleaned.csv\n(/mnt/data/banggood_products_cleaned.csv)"]
    PROC["Data Processing\n(pandas cleaning & feature calc)"]
    DB[(SQLite / CSV storage)]
    APP["streamlit_app.py\n(Streamlit dashboard)"]
    DEP[/"Deployment\nStreamlit Cloud / Heroku"/]
  end

  User[(User / Browser)]

  NB --> CSV
  CSV --> PROC
  PROC --> DB
  PROC --> APP
  DB --> APP
  APP --> User
  Repo --> DEP
  DEP --> APP

  style Repo stroke:#2b6cb0,stroke-width:2px,fill:#f0f8ff
  style User stroke:#38a169,stroke-width:2px,fill:#f0fff4


This project consists of three main components:
- **Web Scraper**: Extracts product data from Banggood using Selenium
- **Data Processing**: Cleans and transforms the raw scraped data
- **Interactive Dashboard**: Visualizes insights through a Streamlit application

## üöÄ Features

### Data Extraction
- Scrapes product data from 5 categories:
  - Chargers
  - RC Cars
  - Multi Rotor Parts
  - Woodworking Clamp
  - Keyboard & Mouse
- Extracts: Product Name, Price, Rating, Reviews, URL
- Handles pagination (2 pages per category)
- Robust error handling and browser management

### Data Processing
- Cleans price data and extracts numeric values
- Processes ratings and review counts
- Creates derived features:
  - Price per Review
  - High Rating Flag
  - Price Categories (Cheap, Moderate, Expensive, Luxury)

### Visualization & Analysis
- Interactive price analysis by category
- Review count distributions
- Price vs Review relationships
- Product rating analysis

## üõ†Ô∏è Installation

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.7+
- Chrome browser

### Setup
```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/banggood-scraper.git
cd banggood-scraper

# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
